# btaa-geo-api-search(1)

## NAME

btaa-geo-api search - search BTAA Geospatial API resources

## SYNOPSIS

`btaa-geo-api search QUERY [--include FIELD=VALUE] [--exclude FIELD=VALUE]`

## DESCRIPTION

Searches `/api/v1/search` and prints a table by default. Use `--output json`, `--output jsonl`, or `--output csv` for machine-readable output.

## OPTIONS

- `--include FIELD=VALUE`: include facet filter. May be repeated.
- `--exclude FIELD=VALUE`: exclude facet filter. May be repeated.
- `--page N`: page number.
- `--per-page N`: results per page.
- `--sort SORT`: relevance, year_desc, year_asc, title_asc, or title_desc.
- `--search-field FIELD`: restrict search to a field.
- `--adv-q JSON`: advanced query JSON array.

## EXAMPLES

```bash
btaa-geo-api search "soil survey"
btaa-geo-api search "seattle" --include gbl_resourceClass_sm=Maps
btaa-geo-api search "seattle" --include dct_spatial_sm=Washington --exclude schema_provider_s="Pennsylvania State University"
btaa-geo-api search "" --adv-q '[{"op":"AND","f":"dct_title_s","q":"Island"}]'
```

## API ENDPOINTS

- `GET /api/v1/search`
- `POST /api/v1/analytics/events`
